## How to Update Supabase Instructions

1. Open HAL app
2. Click "Agent Instructions" button in the header
3. Navigate to: All Agents → QA Agent → QA Audit Report
4. Click "Edit"
5. Add the new "QA Report Template (MANDATORY)" section
6. Update the existing "QA report structure" section to reference the template
7. Save changes (saves directly to Supabase)

## Verification

After updating the instructions, verify:
1. QA agents can access the template at `.cursor/rules/qa-report-template.mdc`
2. QA agents can see the filled examples at `.cursor/rules/qa-report-example-*.mdc`
3. Instructions explicitly state that the template is MANDATORY
4. Instructions explain how to use the template (copy, fill, replace placeholders, publish)
